{
  "question_text": "<p>Given a sorted array of distinct integers and a target value, return the index if the target is found. If not, return the index where it would be if it were inserted in order.</p>\n\n<p>You must&nbsp;write an algorithm with&nbsp;<code>O(log n)</code> runtime complexity.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 1:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> nums = [1,3,5,6], target = 5\n<strong>Output:</strong> 2\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 2:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> nums = [1,3,5,6], target = 2\n<strong>Output:</strong> 1\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 3:</strong></p>\n\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> nums = [1,3,5,6], target = 7\n<strong>Output:</strong> 4\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><code>1 &lt;= nums.length &lt;= 10<sup>4</sup></code></li>\n\t<li><code>-10<sup>4</sup> &lt;= nums[i] &lt;= 10<sup>4</sup></code></li>\n\t<li><code>nums</code> contains <strong>distinct</strong> values sorted in <strong>ascending</strong> order.</li>\n\t<li><code>-10<sup>4</sup> &lt;= target &lt;= 10<sup>4</sup></code></li>\n</ul>\n",
  "difficulty": "EASY",
  "marks": 5,
  "input_format": "Sorted array nums and target",
  "output_format": "Index or insert position",
  "constraints": [
    "1 <= nums.length <= 10^4",
    "-10^4 <= nums[i], target <= 10^4"
  ],
  "explanation": "Standard binary search. If target not found, return left pointer which points to the insertion index.",
  "answer": "def searchInsert(nums, target):\n    l, r = 0, len(nums)-1\n    while l <= r:\n        m = (l+r)//2\n        if nums[m] == target: return m\n        elif nums[m] < target: l = m + 1\n        else: r = m - 1\n    return l",
  "boilerplate": {
    "python": "import sys\nimport json\n\ndef solve(*args):\n    # Implement Search Insert Position here\n    pass\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    data = sys.stdin.read().strip().split('\\n')\n    if not data or data == ['']: sys.exit(0)\n    args = [json.loads(line) for line in data]\n    print(json.dumps(solve(*args)))",
    "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <string>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\nint solve() { return 0; }\nint main() { string line; while (getline(cin, line)) {} return 0; }",
